technical_learnings: JSON-driven checklists take precedence over legacy hardcoded logic in the Orchestrator.
Bypass gaps occur if JSON checklists are not feature-complete with respect to legacy blockers.
Branch-issue coupling must be explicitly enforced to prevent multi-issue pollution.
challenges_overcome: Identified the root cause of the PR Review issue check bypass.
Corrected my own protocol bypass by realigning workspace with a started Beads issue.

process_improvements: Synchronized all legacy mandatory blockers into JSON checklists.
Updated check_beads_issue to enforce 'agent/issue-id' branch pattern and 'started' state.
